backgrounds:
Definition (Cyclotomic harmonic sums; inclusive nesting): Following Ablinger--Blumlein--Schneider, define \cite{ABS1105}
\begin{align}
S_{\{a_1,b_1,c_1\},\dots,\{a_\ell,b_\ell,c_\ell\}}(s_1,\dots,s_\ell;N)
:=\sum_{k_1=1}^{N}\frac{s_1^{k_1}}{(a_1k_1+b_1)^{c_1}}
\,S_{\{a_2,b_2,c_2\},\dots,\{a_\ell,b_\ell,c_\ell\}}(s_2,\dots,s_\ell;k_1),
\qquad S_{\emptyset}=1,
\label{eq:def}
\end{align}
with $a_i,c_i\in\mathbb{N}_{>0}$, $b_i\in\mathbb{N}_{\ge 0}$, $s_i\in\{\pm 1\}$.
Note the \emph{inclusive} upper bound in the recursion: the inner sum runs up to $k_1$ (not $k_1-1$).
Definition (Odd-denominator alternating letter): Introduce the depth-1 sums
\begin{align}
A(N) &:= S_{\{2,1,1\}}(-1;N)=\sum_{k=1}^{N}\frac{(-1)^k}{2k+1},\\
B(N) &:= S_{\{2,1,2\}}(-1;N)=\sum_{k=1}^{N}\frac{(-1)^k}{(2k+1)^2},\\
C(N) &:= S_{\{2,1,3\}}(+1;N)=\sum_{k=1}^{N}\frac{1}{(2k+1)^3}.
\end{align}
Definition (Two depth-2 sums; same letter order swapped): Define
\begin{align}
S_{1,2}(N) &:= S_{\{2,1,1\},\{2,1,2\}}(-1,-1;N)
=\sum_{k_1=1}^{N}\frac{(-1)^{k_1}}{2k_1+1}\sum_{k_2=1}^{k_1}\frac{(-1)^{k_2}}{(2k_2+1)^2},
\label{eq:S12}\\
S_{2,1}(N) &:= S_{\{2,1,2\},\{2,1,1\}}(-1,-1;N)
=\sum_{k_1=1}^{N}\frac{(-1)^{k_1}}{(2k_1+1)^2}\sum_{k_2=1}^{k_1}\frac{(-1)^{k_2}}{2k_2+1}.
\label{eq:S21}
\end{align}
These are genuine nested objects (not a single triangular-region trick), and the \emph{inclusive} nesting matters.

