Definition (planar resolvent and density): Let $\rho(x)$ be a compactly-supported probability density on $\mathbb{R}$ (the large-$N$ eigenvalue density),
and define the resolvent
\begin{equation}\label{eq:resolvent_def}
W(z)\equiv \int_{\mathbb{R}}\frac{\rho(x)}{z-x}\,dx,
\qquad z\in\mathbb{C}\setminus \mathrm{supp}(\rho).
\end{equation}
