W(z)^2 - V'(z)\,W(z) + P(z)=0,
\end{equation}
where $P(z)$ is a polynomial of degree $\deg(V')-2$ fixed uniquely by the asymptotic condition \eqref{eq:asymptotic}.
Definition (one-cut ansatz): Assume the support is a single interval $[a,b]$ and write the standard one-cut form
