Definition (Unitarity condition): Denote the two-to-two partial wave amplitude of scattering $\phi_i \phi_j \rightarrow \phi_k\phi_l$ as $a_{\ell}^{ijkl}$, where $i,j,k,l$ are the indices for scalar field $\phi$. Denote the partial wave amplitude from scattering of $\phi_i \phi_j$ to some intermediate state $X$ as $a_{\ell}^{ij\rightarrow X}$. $a_{\ell}^{ijkl}$ satisfies the following unitarity condition
\begin{equation}
\mathrm{Im} a_{\ell}^{ijkl} = \sum_{mn} \, \eta_{mn} a_{\ell}^{ijmn} \qty(a_{\ell}^{klmn})^* + \sum_{X\neq mn} a_{\ell}^{ij\rightarrow X} \qty(a_{\ell}^{kl\rightarrow X})^*
\end{equation}
where $\eta_{mn}=1$ for $m\neq n$ and $\eta_{mn}=1/2$ for $m=n$.
